play the tape at half speed

00:16:10.560 --> 00:16:13.540
and also play it
at twice speed.

00:16:13.540 --> 00:16:16.240
So let's play the tape.

00:16:16.240 --> 00:16:22.160
And what we have is the
glockenspiel right now

00:16:22.160 --> 00:16:26.540
displayed on a frequency scale
from 0 to 5 kilohertz.

00:16:26.540 --> 00:16:31.210
Let's just change that to
zero to 10 kilohertz.

00:16:31.210 --> 00:16:33.620
So here is this spectrum.

00:16:33.620 --> 00:16:36.950
Over here we have the
time wave form.

00:16:36.950 --> 00:16:40.740
And here is then the first
spectral line, and we can see

00:16:40.740 --> 00:16:44.710
where that is by setting
up the cursor.

00:16:44.710 --> 00:16:48.290
And magically, once again, I
have the cursor positioned at

00:16:48.290 --> 00:16:49.650
just the right spot.

00:16:49.650 --> 00:16:55.120
The first spectral line
is at 1.775 kilohertz.

00:16:55.120 --> 00:17:00.590
And so this is the spectrum
then of the original

00:17:00.590 --> 00:17:02.881
glockenspiel note.

00:17:02.881 --> 00:17:03.320
All right.

00:17:03.320 --> 00:17:07.890
Let's stop the tape
and rewind it.

00:17:07.890 --> 00:17:13.660
And now what we want to do is
play that back at half speed.

00:17:13.660 --> 00:17:16.849
Played at half speed,
the frequencies

00:17:16.849 --> 00:17:18.599
