00:17:22.560 --> 00:17:24.760
at a lower frequency.

00:17:24.760 --> 00:17:27.730
So let's play that now.

00:17:27.730 --> 00:17:29.320
SANDY HILL: There are really
very complicated signals,

00:17:29.320 --> 00:17:30.200
aren't they?

00:17:30.200 --> 00:17:32.760
PROFESSOR: They really are.

00:17:32.760 --> 00:17:37.580
Here we have the first
spectral line.

00:17:37.580 --> 00:17:41.690
And we can compare that with the
